HEADWORD: Mastersinger
<hw>Mas"ter*sing`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A translation
of G. <ets>meisters⟦aum⟧nger</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a class of poets
which flourished in Nuremberg and some other cities of Germany in the
15th and 16th centuries. They bound themselves to observe certain
arbitrary laws of rhythm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

